The {{ill|Kamitsukeno clan|ja|上毛野氏}} is mentioned in several parts of the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀}}, including the story of {{ill|Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto|ja|豊城入彦命}}, the eldest son of Emperor {{ill|Suijin|ja|崇神天皇}}, and his dream<ref>{{Nihon Shoki|Suijin 48th year, 1st month, 10th day}}</ref>, as well as the story of his grandson {{ill|Hikosasima no Ō|ja|彦狭嶋王}} being dispatched along the {{ill|Tōsandō|ja|東山道}}<ref name="#1">{{Nihon Shoki|Keikō 55th year, 2nd month, 5th day}}</ref> and his son {{ill|Mimorowake no Ō|ja|御諸別王}} managing the eastern provinces<ref name="#1"/>. The {{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|ja|新撰姓氏録}} also states that the Kamitsukeno and {{ill|Shimotsukeno Clan|ja|下毛野氏}} were of the same lineage.

