Wakako appears in the Nihon Shoki during the 2nd year of [[Emperor Tenji]] (663), in March, where it states:
{{quotation|The front general {{ill|Kamitsukeno no Wakako|ja|上毛野君稚子|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamitsukeno no Wakako|qq=}}, {{ill|Hashihito no Muraji Ōfuta|ja|間人大蓋|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hashihito no Muraji Ōfuta|qq=}}, middlegenerals {{ill|Kose no Kamusaki no Omi Osamu|ja|巨勢神前訳語|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose no Kamusaki no Omi Osamu|qq=}} and {{ill|Miwa no Kimi Nemaro|ja|三輪根麻呂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miwa no Kimi Nemaro|qq=}}, and rear generals {{ill|Abe no Hiketa no Omi Hirafu|ja|阿倍比羅夫|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Abe no Hiketa no Omi Hirafu|qq=}} and {{ill|Ōyake no Omi Kamatsuka|ja|大宅臣鎌柄|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyake no Omi Kamatsuka|qq=}} were sent with 27,000 troops to attack {{ill|Silla|ja|新羅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Silla|qq=}}.<ref>{{Nihon Shoki|Tenji 2nd year, 3rd month}}</ref>}}

By June of the same year, the generals' forces achieved victory:
{{quotation|They captured two fortresses at {{ill|Sabikinue|ja|沙鼻岐奴江|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sabikinue|qq=}}.<ref>{{Nihon Shoki|Tenji 2nd year, 6th month}}</ref>}}

However, the exact location of "Sabikinue" is debated. If it corresponds to "Sabi" in modern {{ill|Sangju|ja|尚州市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sangju|qq=}}, {{ill|North Gyeongsang Province|ja|慶尚北道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/North Gyeongsang Province|qq=}}, the invasion likely came from the west. Alternatively, if it corresponds to "Sangi" in {{ill|Sangju|ja|三嘉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sangju|qq=}}, {{ill|South Gyeongsang Province|ja|慶尚南道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/South Gyeongsang Province|qq=}}, the invasion may have originated from the south.

The decisive battle of {{ill|Baekgang|ja|白村江|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Baekgang|qq=}} against the {{ill|Tang-Silla Alliance|ja|唐・新羅連合軍|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tang-Silla Alliance|qq=}} occurred two months later.<ref>{{Nihon Shoki|Tenji 2nd year, 8th month, 27th-28th days}}</ref> Wakako’s role in this final battle and his fate remain unknown.

In the 13th year of Emperor {{ill|Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmu|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|qq=}} (684), the {{ill|Eight Kabane|ja|八色の姓|1=Eight Kabane system|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eight Kabane|13=User:Immanuelle/Eight Kabane system|qq=}} were established, and the Kamitsukeno Clan received the title of {{ill|Ason|ja|朝臣|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ason|qq=}} in recognition of their longstanding contributions to the court, including the service of {{ill|Kamitsukeno no Mikoto no Miko no Mitsumaro|ja|上毛野三千|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamitsukeno no Mikoto no Miko no Mitsumaro|qq=}}.<ref>{{Nihon Shoki|Tenmu 13th year, 11th month, 1st day}}</ref>

