'''Kamitsukeno no Wakako''' (上毛野 稚子, birth and death years unknown) was a nobleman from the [[Asuka period]] of Japan. His family name was [[:en:Kimi (kabane)|Kimi]].
== Career == The {{ill|Kamitsukeno clan|ja|上毛野氏|1=Kamitsukeno clan|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamitsukeno clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamitsukeno clan|qq=}} is mentioned in several parts of the [[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]], including the story of {{ill|Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto|ja|豊城入彦命|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyokiirihiko-no-mikoto|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|qq=}}, the eldest son of Emperor [[:en:Emperor Sujin|Suijin]], and his dream<ref>{{Nihon Shoki|Suijin 48th year, 1st month, 10th day}}</ref>, as well as the story of his grandson {{ill|Hikosashima no Ōkimi|lt=Hikosashima no Ōkimi|lt=Hikosasima no Ō|ja|彦狭嶋王|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikosasima no Ō|qq=}} being dispatched along the [[:en:Tōsandō|Tōsandō]]<ref name="#1">{{Nihon Shoki|Keikō 55th year, 2nd month, 5th day}}</ref> and his son {{ill|Mimorowake no Ō|ja|御諸別王|1=Mimorowake|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mimorowake no Ō|13=User:Immanuelle/Mimorowake|qq=}} managing the eastern provinces<ref name="#1"/>. The [[:en:Shinsen Shōjiroku|Shinsen Shōjiroku]] also states that the Kamitsukeno and {{ill|Shimotsukeno Clan|ja|下毛野氏|1=Shimotsukeno clan|lt=Shimotsukeno clan|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimotsukeno Clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimotsukeno clan|qq=}} were of the same lineage.
Wakako appears in the Nihon Shoki during the 2nd year of [[Emperor Tenji]] (663), in March, where it states: {{quotation|The front general {{ill|Kamitsukeno no Wakatoko|lt=Kamitsukeno no Wakatoko|lt=Kamitsukeno no Wakako|ja|上毛野君稚子|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamitsukeno no Wakako|qq=}}, {{ill|Hashihito no Muraji Ōfuta|ja|間人大蓋|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hashihito no Muraji Ōfuta|qq=}}, middlegenerals {{ill|Kose no Kamusaki no Omi Osamu|ja|巨勢神前訳語|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose no Kamusaki no Omi Osamu|qq=}} and {{ill|Miwa no Kimi Nemaro|ja|三輪根麻呂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miwa no Kimi Nemaro|qq=}}, and rear generals [[:en:Abe no Hirafu|Abe no Hiketa no Omi Hirafu]] and {{ill|Ōyake no Omi Kamatsuka|ja|大宅臣鎌柄|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyake no Omi Kamatsuka|qq=}} were sent with 27,000 troops to attack [[:en:Silla|Silla]].<ref>{{Nihon Shoki|Tenji 2nd year, 3rd month}}</ref>}}
By June of the same year, the generals' forces achieved victory: {{quotation|They captured two fortresses at {{ill|Sabikinue|ja|沙鼻岐奴江|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sabikinue|qq=}}.<ref>{{Nihon Shoki|Tenji 2nd year, 6th month}}</ref>}}
However, the exact location of "Sabikinue" is debated. If it corresponds to "Sabi" in modern [[:en:Sangju|Sangju]], [[:en:North Gyeongsang Province|North Gyeongsang Province]], the invasion likely came from the west. Alternatively, if it corresponds to "Sangi" in {{ill|Sangju|ja|三嘉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sangju|qq=}}, [[:en:South Gyeongsang Province|South Gyeongsang Province]], the invasion may have originated from the south.
The decisive battle of {{ill|Baekgang|ja|白村江|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Baekgang|qq=}} against the {{ill|Tang-Silla Alliance|ja|唐・新羅連合軍|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tang-Silla Alliance|qq=}} occurred two months later.<ref>{{Nihon Shoki|Tenji 2nd year, 8th month, 27th-28th days}}</ref> Wakako’s role in this final battle and his fate remain unknown.
In the 13th year of Emperor {{ill|Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmu|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|qq=}} (684), the {{ill|Eight Kabane|ja|八色の姓|1=Eight Kabane system|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eight Kabane|13=User:Immanuelle/Eight Kabane system|qq=}} were established, and the Kamitsukeno Clan received the title of [[:en:Ason|Ason]] in recognition of their longstanding contributions to the court, including the service of {{ill|Kamitsukeno no Michichi|lt=Kamitsukeno no Michichi|lt=Kamitsukeno no Mikoto no Miko no Mitsumaro|ja|上毛野三千|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamitsukeno no Mikoto no Miko no Mitsumaro|qq=}}.<ref>{{Nihon Shoki|Tenmu 13th year, 11th month, 1st day}}</ref>
